# Configuring a Local DNF/RPM Repository on RHEL

This guide explains how to configure a local DNF/RPM repository using RHEL installation media. This is essential for environments without internet access or for optimizing package installation speeds.

---

## 🚀 Step-by-Step Instructions

### 1. Create a Mount Point
Create a directory where the installation media (ISO) will be mounted.
```bash
sudo mkdir -p /mnt/disc

# If using a physical drive or virtual CD-ROM
sudo mount /dev/cdrom /mnt/disc

Create a new .repo file in the /etc/yum.repos.d/ directory
**Extension of the file must set to .repo, otherwise it will not work.
sudo vi /etc/yum.repos.d/local.repo

## Add the following configuration on /etc/yum.repos.d/

[local-baseos]
name=RHEL Local Repository - BaseOS
baseurl=file:///mnt/disc/BaseOS
enabled=1
gpgcheck=0

[local-appstream]
name=RHEL Local Repository - AppStream
baseurl=file:///mnt/disc/AppStream
enabled=1
gpgcheck=0
